Summaries

three sample summaries

[1] He shared three stories from his life. The first is “connecting the dots”. He didn't see the value in being at university and dropped out. And from that, that leads to a life that cannot be called rich. However, by taking a calligraphy class in college, that knowledge later led to the creation of multiple typefaces and spacing fonts for the Mac. by following my curiosity and intuition, many of the things I came across later turned into things of great value. You cannot look ahead to the future and try to connect the dots. All we can do is look back at the past and connect the dots. Soyou have to believe that the dots will somehow connect in the future.The second story is about love and loss. I was fired from my company when I was 30 years old. However, I really liked what I was doing so I was able to go back to basics and start a new company. You have to find something that you absolutely love, whether it's love or work. The third story is about death. Living with death in mind is the best way to avoid the pitfall of thinking you have something to lose.
[2] Steve Jobs gave a speech where he told three important stories from his life. Firstly, he talked about "connecting the dots." He dropped out of college because he didn’t see the value. But, after he left, he realized that the calligraphy class he took helped him design the first Macintosh computer. He said that sometimes you can only understand how things fit together when you look back at them. The second story was about "love and loss." After being fired from Apple, he felt despair. But, he started new companies named NeXT and Pixar. He said it's important to find what you love and keep going. Finally, he spoke about "death." When he was diagnosed with cancer, he realized how short life is. He told everyone to follow their hearts and live the life they truly want. He was saying at the end of the speech, "Stay hungry, stay foolish."                                                                                                                                                                                                                                
[3] > Jobs made three main points. Firstly, though Steve Jobs’ biological mother wanted his adoptive parents to finish college level education, neither of them did graduate from college. They promised his biological mother that Jobs would go to college someday. Jobs went to Reed college, but dropped out after 6 months since he could not see any value in it. Thanks to the decision, regardless of anxiety, he could attend the classes that really interested him. He found calligraphy fascinating, and the time he spent there led to the functions that he put for the computer he invented. Secondly, he talked about his experiences of getting fired from Apple. Although it was devastating for him, it was a great chance for him to realise he loved what he did. Thirdly, he mentioned his disease and his experience of feeling death close to him. He thinks that the idea of death can help us see what is most important for us now, clearing unnecessary noises. <
